HEADWORD: Scarus
<hw>Sca"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Scar</er> a kind of fish.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
Mediterranean food fish (<spn>Sparisoma scarus</spn>) of excellent
quality and highly valued by the Romans; -- called also <altname>parrot
fish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

